1 the following procedures are strictly adhered to with respect to the
2 Oklahoma Department of Mental Health and Substance Abuse Services:
3 1. In accordance with paragraph 3 of subsection A of Section
4 34.6 of this title, prior to releasing the one-twelfth (1/12)
5 appropriations disbursement, OMES shall conduct a review of the
6 agency's budget to actuals to ensure the agency is staying within
7 budget constraints;
8 2. OMES shall provide a report to the Governor, the Speaker of
9 the Oklahoma House of Representatives, the President Pro Tempore of
10 the Oklahoma State Senate, and the chairs and vice-chairs of the
11 standing committees of the Oklahoma House of Representatives and the
12 Oklahoma State Senate having primary responsibility for the
13 consideration of agency appropriations concerning the status of
14 revenue and expenditures of the agency;
15 3. The Oklahoma Department of Mental Health and Substance Abuse
16 Services shall be prohibited from entering into contracts that do
17 not clearly state a maximum fiscal obligation;
18 4. OMES shall review encumbrances for any multi-year purchase
19 orders or contracts to ensure that only the anticipated amount of
20 funds for the current fiscal year are encumbered; and
21 5. OMES shall prohibit the processing of payments for non-
22 budgeted expenditures.
23 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
24 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
